    <!-- Problems Section -->
    <section class="problems-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px;">
                <h2>What Are the Top 5 Appliance Problems in Whitby?</h2>
                <p class="section-subtitle">Learn how to fix urgent issues specific to Whitby homes: lake humidity damage, large-capacity appliances, mixed construction types, and suburban family needs.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="problems-grid">
                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🌊</div>
                    <h3>How to Fix Lake Ontario Humidity Damage Destroying Whitby Appliances?</h3>
                    <p><strong>Whitby Challenge:</strong> Proximity to Lake Ontario creates elevated humidity levels (60-80% vs. 40-50% ideal) that cause urgent stress on appliances. Metal components rust faster, electronic control boards corrode, refrigerator gaskets develop mold, and dryer vents accumulate moisture causing extended dry times and fire hazards. <strong>What Causes This:</strong> Constant moisture exposure from lake-effect weather accelerates wear and corrosion. <strong>How to Fix It:</strong> Rust removal and protective coatings, control board cleaning/replacement, gasket replacement with mold-resistant seals, dryer vent cleaning and moisture barrier installation, dehumidification recommendations. <strong>Cost: $180-$420.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">👨‍👩‍👧‍👦</div>
                    <h3>How to Repair Large-Capacity Appliances for Growing Whitby Families?</h3>
                    <p><strong>Whitby Challenge:</strong> Whitby's rapidly growing population (population 138,000+) means many homes have 3-5 person families using large-capacity washers (5.0+ cu ft), double ovens, and oversized refrigerators. Heavy daily use causes accelerated wear: bearing failures in washers from overloading, uneven heating in large ovens, and compressor strain in oversized fridges running constantly. <strong>What Causes Failures:</strong> Continuous heavy-duty operation beyond standard residential use patterns. <strong>How to Fix It:</strong> Heavy-duty bearing and suspension system replacement, load balancing and calibration, dual compressor diagnostics and repair, heating element replacement for even cooking, energy efficiency optimization. <strong>Cost: $220-$480.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🏘️</div>
                    <h3>Mixing Old and New Construction Appliances in Whitby Homes</h3>
                    <p><strong>Whitby Challenge:</strong> Whitby has diverse housing stock from 1970s-80s Brooklin heritage homes to brand new Port Whitby developments. Older homes often have vintage appliances (30+ years old) with discontinued parts, while new homes have ultra-modern smart appliances. This creates repair challenges: sourcing obsolete parts for vintage units, troubleshooting complex smart appliance electronics, adapting modern appliances to old electrical systems (60-amp vs 200-amp), and incompatible water pressure/gas lines. <strong>Our Solution:</strong> Extensive vintage parts network and fabrication capability, smart appliance diagnostic equipment and training, electrical system assessment and upgrade recommendations, plumbing/gas line compatibility evaluation. <strong>Typical Cost: $200-$450.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🚗</div>
                    <h3>How to Service Suburban Appliance Accessibility Issues in Whitby?</h3>
                    <p><strong>Whitby Challenge:</strong> Whitby's suburban layout means many homes have appliances in challenging locations: stacked washer/dryers in second-floor laundry rooms, built-in appliances requiring custom removal, garage and basement workshop appliances, and tight kitchen layouts in newer townhomes. These create urgent access and service difficulties. <strong>What Makes Repairs Difficult:</strong> Limited workspace, risk of damage during removal, specialized tools needed. <strong>How We Handle It:</strong> Stacked unit separation and reassembly expertise, built-in appliance extraction without cabinet damage, portable lift equipment for heavy appliances, tight-space diagnostic tools and techniques. <strong>Cost: $190-$400.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">❄️</div>
                    <h3>How to Fix Winter-Damaged Appliances After Cold Whitby Winters?</h3>
                    <p><strong>Whitby Challenge:</strong> Harsh Durham Region winters (-20°C to -30°C cold snaps) cause specific appliance failures: frozen water supply lines to refrigerators and dishwashers, garage freezers failing to start in extreme cold, dryer exhaust vents freezing shut causing poor performance, and condensation damage when bringing cold appliances into warm homes. <strong>What Causes Winter Failures:</strong> Extreme temperature fluctuations stress components and freeze water systems. <strong>How to Fix It:</strong> Water line thawing and insulation installation, garage-rated appliance recommendations or heating solutions, vent de-icing and insulated vent installation, condensation damage repair and prevention strategies. <strong>Cost: $160-$380.</strong></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="emergency-cta-box">
                <h3>Whitby Appliance Repair Experts</h3>
                <p>Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, GE, and all major brands. Lake humidity solutions, family-sized appliances, old & new construction specialists. Same-day service available, 90-day warranty.</p>
                <a href="tel:437-747-6737" class="emergency-phone-btn">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
